      "line": 11,
      "message": "It is just a developer aid for testing with no functional value other than a quick way to massage it for particular testing the developer may want to do.    It is out of intent and scope cover all variations possible.   I could remove it and let developer figure out basic structure, but this is far more convenient so a developer can have quickly accessible to massage it and use it for manual tests.\n\nSee my answer to Daniel from before in the review:\n---\n*.properties or their rest variant *.rest.json (for on the fly loading) is work in progress, will be adding right parameters as we go through making sure the use cases work.\nThis is a general comment for all files in config directory of archetype, specially sample messages, developers will change and modify for their own testing.   It is though important that the information there is correct such as the VF having to be VNF.\n----",
